I too remember walking across the Charles Bridge on a visit to Prague about 15 years ago. To be honest, I have zero independent recollection of its Czech name, but a little research indicates it is “Karlův most.” Nevertheless, Googling the name “Karel” reveals that seems to be the Czech version of “Charles”. Interesting factoid: on July 9, 2017 Google celebrated the 660th anniversary of the start of its construction with a really nice looking “Google Doodle”. See:

