@Barry Ancona so if not then all Marx brothers are common knowledge? Zeppo is the answer in my other puzzle. So I either need to memorize all 5 brothers or just auto solve going forward? No fun in that. Just annoying.  What about Karl Marx's brother? Should we also know Hermann? Shout out to Hermann Marx.

The reply is usually akin to "It's a puzzle" - right but there's a difference between difficulty and obscurity. This clue isn't hard in a satisfying way. Clues like these are what tank some puzzles for me. How about instead of Harpo we use harpy, how about instead of Zeppo - zippo? Let's raise the bar of our cluing and avoid the need for rote proper noun memorization. 

But I think some enjoy this memorizing, and I'm sure some were around for the Marx brothers. So I'll show my age here and respect my elders. I will die on this anti proper noun hill though. Poetically this may come full circle on me years from now, some day I'll be on here defending the a Jonas brothers clueing. . . It's usually Joe . . .

